{"TopicId":147486,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Tweakable craft lighting.","CreatedByName":"dpatt711","CreatedById":70543,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-12T01:40:11Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"dpatt711","CreatedById":70543,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-12T01:40:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be cool to see tweakable lighting in Stock KSP. Allowing users to edit basic things like beam width, focus, intensity and color.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Atlas2342","CreatedById":155194,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-12T02:23:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, you can already edit the color and somehow, the intensity. Just right-click on the lights.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jonfliesgoats","CreatedById":168077,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-13T00:12:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere was a navigation lights mod on PC too. \u00A0That would be handy for stock, especially docking on the night side of Kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-13T03:09:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222753139\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147486\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473725529\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168077\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jonfliesgoats\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Jonfliesgoats said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere was a navigation lights mod on PC too. \u00A0That would be handy for stock, especially docking on the night side of Kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor docking purposes, \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/137806-113-indicatorlights-v10-small-convenient-informative/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EIndicatorLights\u003C/a\u003E can be handy, too.\u00A0 Illuminated indicators for docking ports.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022docking%20ports.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://raw.githubusercontent.com/KSPSnark/IndicatorLights/master/screenshots/docking%20ports.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jonfliesgoats","CreatedById":168077,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-13T09:35:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like those! \u00A0They look just like form(formation)\u00A0lighting on NATO aircraft, which serve the exact same function.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dpatt711","CreatedById":70543,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-14T12:46:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222751814\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147486\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473646999\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155194\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Atlas2342\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/11/2016 at 10:23 PM, Atlas2342 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, you can already edit the color and somehow, the intensity. Just right-click on the lights.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould still be nice to have better intensity adjustment, and ability to edit beam width and focus.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-14T13:43:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nColor is tweakable. Power - just go with all color sliders more towards \u0022black\u0022. The two stock reflectors have two different beam widths. Focus and fully tweakable width? *shrug* maybe...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI somewhat wish for a stock omni-light - something to make \u0022lanterns\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-14T13:44:31Z\u0022 title=\u002209/14/2016 01:44  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 14, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Sharpy\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}